HEADWORD: Turacin
<hw>Tu"ra*cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A red or crimson pigment obtained from certain
feathers of several species of <prodby>turacou</prodby>; whence the
name. It contains nearly six per cent of copper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

